external_knowledge:
- "top three spenders" means the customers with the highest total spent; 
- "orders out for delivery" refers to orders with a status of 'Out for Delivery';
- "successfully paid" means the payment status is 'Paid'.

- "Journey of transformation" refers to orders where the status has changed; 
- "Metamorphosis" indicates a significant change in the status of an order; 
- "Identities" include usernames, customer names, and product names; 
- "Financial details" encompass total amount and any discount applied; 
- "Milestones of payment and shipping" refer to payment and shipping statuses.

sql:
SELECT c.first_name, c.last_name
FROM customers c
JOIN orders o ON c.customer_id = o.customer_id
WHERE o.total_amount = (
    SELECT MAX(total_amount) FROM orders
);

SELECT c.first_name, c.last_name, o.status
FROM customers c
JOIN orders o ON c.customer_id = o.customer_id;
